      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DRIVE TO THE BEACH (1) added to a series of top-four finishes with another good performance last time out for third at this circuit and distance, beaten 3.4 metres. Gets the ace draw and came from there when third in stronger company three back. Race fit now so could break through. TAKE OUT (10) comes through the Honouree Stakes series where he was runner up in his heat and midfield in the final at his latest appearance, beaten 5.6 metres. Drops in grade so with even luck from the back row has the ability to take this out. THE ROGUE I AM (7) did some work last time so it may pay to forgive that and assess her chances off a good effort here two back when beaten only 2m from this barrier. THEYCALLMEBRUCE (3) has been coming from wider or second row barriers of late so should not have any excuses from this more favourable draw.",
